Program: Outlook
Title: 02/04/2012
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00q87n7
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 3 Apr 2012
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, 30 years after the start of the Falklands War, we hear how two enemy soldiers were brought together by a lost camera. Also, as the cherry blossom front moves northwards in Japan, we get a glimpse into the remarkable world of the geisha and their traditional cherry blossom dances. And we meet Lina al Maeena, a Saudi woman who overcame religious objections and set up a basketball team for women. Show less